    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:1",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Pain control (acute pain, chronic pain)    Assessment:     right rib fractures #",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s1",
      "text": "Pain control (acute pain, chronic pain)    Assessment:     right rib fractures #[**6-2**], pnx, and 2 CT.  rated pain [**8-31**] when    coughing and deep breathing."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:2",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Action:    -Tordol extended for another 3 days    - Dilaudid given prn    - Dila",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s2",
      "text": "Action:    -Tordol extended for another 3 days    - Dilaudid given prn    - Dilaudid pca started .12/6/1.2    - Tylenol 1gm ATC    - neurontin started    - lidocain patch on 8pm/ off 8am    - bowel regime ( senna and colace) started    - OOB    - family at bedside    Response:    Better pain control with PCA, pt using appropriately, rates pain at 3    when coughing instead of a [**8-31**] before PCA."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:3",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Plan:    Cont pain assessment, encourage pt to voice pain, pre medicate before  ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s3",
      "text": "Plan:    Cont pain assessment, encourage pt to voice pain, pre medicate before    turns."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:4",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Respiratory failure, acute (not ARDS/[**Doctor Last Name 76**])    Assessment:  ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s4",
      "text": "Respiratory failure, acute (not ARDS/[**Doctor Last Name 76**])    Assessment:    HX of emphysema (COPD)  s/p fall and sustained right rib fractures #    [**6-2**] and a large PTX . pt has 2 CT , + fluct, no leaks, + sq emphysema    in chest, and arms, lung sounds decreased on right and exp wheeze on    left."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:5",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "On 3L nc.",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s5",
      "text": "On 3L nc."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:6",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Action:    -          Albuterol, ipatropium nebs ATC    -          OOB to chair ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s6",
      "text": "Action:    -          Albuterol, ipatropium nebs ATC    -          OOB to chair    -          IS and C&DB    -          CT to H2o seal this am    -          CXR done    -          Ct from OSH d/c ( right anteroir)    -          O2 weaned to tolerate sat low 90 s to high 80    Response:    With better pain control pt able to cough more effectively and    productively."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:7",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Sat low 90 s. tolerating OOB to chair well.",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s7",
      "text": "Sat low 90 s. tolerating OOB to chair well."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row730292:8",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Plan:    Cont pulm toilet, Tx to floor in am.",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row730292#s8",
      "text": "Plan:    Cont pulm toilet, Tx to floor in am."
    }
